    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i keep getting a MemoryError when i try to run this script that processes a huge csv file using pandas. i think it's because i'm loading everything into a list at once. what's the actual difference between using a list comprehension vs a generator function when it comes to memory usage? i need to fix this before the deployment tomorrow.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The core difference lies in how they handle data: list comprehensions build and store the entire sequence in memory at once, consuming significant RAM for large datasets. Generators, conversely, yield items one by one as they are requested, meaning only one item exists in memory at any given time. For massive CSV files, using a generator is vastly superior because it processes data lazily, preventing the `MemoryError`. You should switch your processing to iterate over a generator instead of building a large list.",
      "source": "target",
