      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if i switch to a generator, i won't be holding the whole file in RAM anymore. but i'm still seeing some strange spikes in memory usage even when i'm not using big lists. like, it feels like something is just eating up the resources in the background. how do i check if i actually have a memory leak or if it's just how python manages objects?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To diagnose this, use Python's `tracemalloc` module to track memory allocations, or profile your script with tools like `memory_profiler`. This will show you exactly which lines of code are consuming the most memory over time. Sometimes, memory spikes are due to temporary objects or caching mechanisms in libraries like Pandas, not necessarily a leak. If the usage climbs continuously without leveling off, a leak is likely occurring.",
      "source": "target",
