    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If memory seems to vanish without a clear process change, it often relates to operating system memory management or garbage collection cycles rather than a deterministic leak. Use your system's resource monitor (like Task Manager on Windows or Activity Monitor on macOS) to see if the peak usage reported by Python is truly being released to the OS immediately. Sometimes, the OS \"reclaims\" memory it gave to the process even if Python hasn't explicitly freed it, making it look like it disappeared.",
      "source": "target",
